                            <comment id="17921549" author="dcapwell" created="Mon, 27 Jan 2025 21:37:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20069&quot; title=&quot;Improve Accord Work Queueing (and misc perf improvements)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-20069&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-20069&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; refactored jvm-dtest which caused this test to fail.  Alex/Benedict/I talked about it and the following is what we talked about&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;1) the change was trying to cleanup the logic where we try to find the right cluster, and make sure we call JVMStabilityInspector correctly.  This logic basically tries to solve &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19515&quot; title=&quot;unhandled exception handling in jvm dtest may see errors from other clusters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19515&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-19515&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
2) the change to mark corruption as unhandled was not intentional, and Alex/Benedict are +0 to going back to the old semantic.&lt;br/&gt;
3) &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20069&quot; title=&quot;Improve Accord Work Queueing (and misc perf improvements)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-20069&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-20069&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; moved to using reflection to call JVMStabilityInspector rather than Instance.uncaughtException, this can become an issue for upgrade tests when and if that internal class has a API change... we should revert back to using Instance.uncaughtException to avoid breaking upgrade tests in the future&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
